prodInfoDesc.name: prodInfoDesc
prodInfoDesc.description: A textual description of the software release. Includes the release level and the internal revision level (example: SNA/net Release 5R2 Revision 5.2.10 Installed 06/03/94 07:10 ).

prodInfoFeatures.name: prodInfoFeatures
prodInfoFeatures.description: A value which indicates the features included in the software release. The value is a sum. This sum initially takes the value zero, then for each feature a value is assigned corresponding to a power of 2, such that a unique number is generated for each combination of features. Feature 1 Cross-Domain Resource Manager 2 Terminal Connect 4 PU T2.0 Inverted 8 Node Type 2.1 Low Entry Node (len) 16 Network Packet-Switching Interface (NPSI) 32 Remote Batch File Transfer Extended (RBFTE)

t5nodeTable.name: t5nodeTable
t5nodeTable.description: This table contains information about the Type 5 node functionality (SSCP) provided by the SNA/net product. Multiple nodes can be provided by a single SNA/net product.

t5nodeEntry.name: t5nodeEntry
t5nodeEntry.description: Entry contains information about the Type 5 node functionality (SSCP).

t5nodeIndex.name: t5nodeIndex
t5nodeIndex.description: SNA/net can appear as more than one t5node. Used to index instances of this object. Value is assigned by the agent and remains constant.

t5nodeDomainName.name: t5nodeDomainName
t5nodeDomainName.description: The configured name for this domain. This is also the t5nodeSscpName, if t5nodeSscpName is a 0 length string.

t5nodeOperState.name: t5nodeOperState
t5nodeOperState.description: The operational state of the Type 5 Domain.

t5nodeSubareaNumber.name: t5nodeSubareaNumber
t5nodeSubareaNumber.description: The subarea number for this domain.

t5nodeSscpName.name: t5nodeSscpName
t5nodeSscpName.description: The name of the SSCP. Must be unique in the SNA subnetwork. It must match the name of the VTAM CDRM macro that defines this t5node as a CDRM to VTAM. May be a zero length string, in which case, the t5nodeDomainName is the name of the SSCP.

t5nodeSscpId.name: t5nodeSscpId
t5nodeSscpId.description: This value is used in ACTCDRM messages sent to VTAM.

t5nodePuName.name: t5nodePuName
t5nodePuName.description: The PU identifier of this node.

t5CdrmTable.name: t5CdrmTable
t5CdrmTable.description: This table contains information about other Crossdomain Resource Managers known to this type 5 node.

t5CdrmEntry.name: t5CdrmEntry
t5CdrmEntry.description: The entry contains information about CDRMs. Variables have read-only access. The variable t5CdrmAdminState has read-write access and is used to control a CDRM.

t5CdrmT5nodeIndex.name: t5CdrmT5nodeIndex
t5CdrmT5nodeIndex.description: Index in the t5nodetable of the t5node this CDRM is associated with.

t5CdrmName.name: t5CdrmName
t5CdrmName.description: The configured name of the CDRM.

t5CdrmSnaName.name: t5CdrmSnaName
t5CdrmSnaName.description: The name of the CDRM as it is known in the SNA network. May be a zero length string, in which case, the t5CdrmName is the SNA name.

t5CdrmAdminState.name: t5CdrmAdminState
t5CdrmAdminState.description: Used by the Management Station to control the CDRM. Values up (2) and down (3) can be read or written, while value other (1) is read-only and indicates that this variable has not been set since reboot.

t5CdrmOperState.name: t5CdrmOperState
t5CdrmOperState.description: The current operational state of the CDRM in relation to this Type 5 node SSCP.

t5CdrmSubareaNumber.name: t5CdrmSubareaNumber
t5CdrmSubareaNumber.description: The subarea number for the CDRM.

t5CdrmNetworkName.name: t5CdrmNetworkName
t5CdrmNetworkName.description: The SNA network name for the CDRM.

t5CdrmElementAddress.name: t5CdrmElementAddress
t5CdrmElementAddress.description: Element Address assigned to this CDRM.

t5CdrscTable.name: t5CdrscTable
t5CdrscTable.description: This table contains information about other Crossdomain Resources known to this type 5 node.

t5CdrscEntry.name: t5CdrscEntry
t5CdrscEntry.description: The entry contains information about a CDRSC. Variables have read-only access. The variable t5CdrscAdminState has read-write access and is used to control a CDRSC.

t5CdrscT5nodeIndex.name: t5CdrscT5nodeIndex
t5CdrscT5nodeIndex.description: Index in the t5nodetable of the t5node this CDRSC is associated with.

t5CdrscName.name: t5CdrscName
t5CdrscName.description: The configured name of the CDRSC.

t5CdrscSnaName.name: t5CdrscSnaName
t5CdrscSnaName.description: The name of the CDRSC as it is known in the SNA Network. The SnaName is the same a the t5CdrscName when this value is a zero length string.

t5CdrscCdrmName.name: t5CdrscCdrmName
t5CdrscCdrmName.description: The name the CDRM which owns this CDRSC.

t5CdrscAdminState.name: t5CdrscAdminState
t5CdrscAdminState.description: Used by the Management Station to control the use of the CDRSC. Values up (2) and down (3) may be read or written, while the value other(1) read-only and indicates this variable has not been set since the last reboot.

t5CdrscOperState.name: t5CdrscOperState
t5CdrscOperState.description: The current operational state of the CDRSC in relation to this Type 5 node SSCP.

t5CdrscSessions.name: t5CdrscSessions
t5CdrscSessions.description: The number of active SNA LU-LU sessions for this CDRSC.

t5CdrscDlmName.name: t5CdrscDlmName
t5CdrscDlmName.description: The name of the Default Logon mode table used by this CDRSC.

t5CdrscCosName.name: t5CdrscCosName
t5CdrscCosName.description: The name of the Class of Service table used by this CDRSC.

t5DlmTable.name: t5DlmTable
t5DlmTable.description: This table contains information about Default Logon Mode Tables used by the SSCP for LU-LU session establishment.

t5DlmEntry.name: t5DlmEntry
t5DlmEntry.description: The entry contains a Default Logon Mode Table entry. All variables are read-only.

t5DlmT5nodeIndex.name: t5DlmT5nodeIndex
t5DlmT5nodeIndex.description: Index in the t5nodetable of the t5node this DLM is associated with.

t5DlmName.name: t5DlmName
t5DlmName.description: The configured name of the Default Logon Mode.

t5DlmSnaName.name: t5DlmSnaName
t5DlmSnaName.description: The name of the Default Logon Mode as it is known in the SNA network. May contain a zero length string, in which case, the t5DlmName is the SNA name.

t5DlmFmprof.name: t5DlmFmprof
t5DlmFmprof.description: The Function Management Profile type, a value from 0 to 18 hexadecimal(byte 1 in the session parameter field).

t5DlmTsprof.name: t5DlmTsprof
t5DlmTsprof.description: The Transmission Services profile type, a value from 1 to 17 hexadecimal(byte 2 in the session parameter field).

t5DlmPriprot.name: t5DlmPriprot
t5DlmPriprot.description: The primary logical unit protocol, a value from 0 to 0FF hexadecimal(byte 3 in the session parameter field).

t5DlmSecprot.name: t5DlmSecprot
t5DlmSecprot.description: The secondary logical unit protocol, a value from 0 to 0FF hexadecimal(byte 4 in the session parameter field).

t5DlmComprot.name: t5DlmComprot
t5DlmComprot.description: The common logical unit protocol, a value from 0 to 0FFFF hexadecimal(byte 5 and 6 in the session parameter field).

t5DlmRusizes.name: t5DlmRusizes
t5DlmRusizes.description: The maximum length of data request units in bytes. A four digit hexadecimal value is provided in the same format as for the ACF/VTAM generation(bytes 9 and 10 in the session parameter field.

t5DlmPservic.name: t5DlmPservic
t5DlmPservic.description: The logical unit presentation services profile and usage field(bytes 13 through 24 in the session parameter field). A 24 digit hexadecimal number.

t5DlmPsndpac.name: t5DlmPsndpac
t5DlmPsndpac.description: The primary send pacing count(byte 11 in the session parameter field), a value from 0 to 63 decimal.

t5DlmPrcvpac.name: t5DlmPrcvpac
t5DlmPrcvpac.description: The primary receive pacing count(byte 12 in the session parameter field), a value from 0 to 63 decimal.

t5DlmSsndpac.name: t5DlmSsndpac
t5DlmSsndpac.description: The secondary send pacing count(byte 7 in the session parameter field), a value from 0 to 63 decimal.

t5DlmSrcvpac.name: t5DlmSrcvpac
t5DlmSrcvpac.description: The secondary receive pacing count(byte 8 in the session parameter field), a value from 0 to 63 decimal.

t5DlmEncr.name: t5DlmEncr
t5DlmEncr.description: The encryption/decryption type expected by the logical unit(first four bits of byte 26 in the session parameter field), a value from 0 to F hexadecimal.

t5DlmBindType.name: t5DlmBindType
t5DlmBindType.description: The BIND type, a value of 0 or 1. 0 means a negotiable BIND 1 means a non-negotiable BIND.

t5DlmCos.name: t5DlmCos
t5DlmCos.description: The name of the class of service to be used for a session that uses this logon mode.

t5CosTable.name: t5CosTable
t5CosTable.description: This table contain class of service (COS) entries.

t5CosEntry.name: t5CosEntry
t5CosEntry.description: The entry contains a class of service entry. All variables are read-only.

t5CosT5nodeIndex.name: t5CosT5nodeIndex
t5CosT5nodeIndex.description: Index in the t5nodetable of the t5node this COS is associated with.

t5CosName.name: t5CosName
t5CosName.description: The configured name of the class of service entry.

t5CosSnaName.name: t5CosSnaName
t5CosSnaName.description: The name of the class of service entry as it is known in the SNA Network. May be a zero length string, in which case, the t5CosName is the SNA name.

t5CosVrids.name: t5CosVrids
t5CosVrids.description: A list of virtual routes, in hierarchical order, that are used for LU-LU session traffic. The list is octet pairs in the form x,y where x is the virtual route number from 0 to 7, and y is the transmission priority from 0 to 3. Up to 24 ordered pairs are possible (vr1,tp1 vr2,tp2 ...vr24,tp24).

t5AliasTable.name: t5AliasTable
t5AliasTable.description: This table is a crossreference for alias names to SNA/net resource names. The current use of this table is for alternate logon names for Crossdomain resources.

t5AliasEntry.name: t5AliasEntry
t5AliasEntry.description: The entry contains the alias name and a reference to the SNA (CDRSC) resource it refers to. All variables are read-only.

t5AliasT5nodeIndex.name: t5AliasT5nodeIndex
t5AliasT5nodeIndex.description: Index in the t5nodetable of the t5node this Alias Name is associated with.

t5AliasResourceId.name: t5AliasResourceId
t5AliasResourceId.description: A reference to the SNA resource (CDRSC) identified by this Alias Name. It is the object identifier representing the instance of the index variable of the resource.

saErTable.name: saErTable
saErTable.description: This table contains information about explicit routes between this subarea and other network subareas.

saErEntry.name: saErEntry
saErEntry.description: This entry contain information about an explicit route.

saErT5nodeIndex.name: saErT5nodeIndex
saErT5nodeIndex.description: Index in the t5nodetable of the t5node this explicit route is associated with.

saErDestinationSubarea.name: saErDestinationSubarea
saErDestinationSubarea.description: The destination subarea number for this Expicit Route.

saErNumber.name: saErNumber
saErNumber.description: The number of the Explicit Route.

saErTgNumber.name: saErTgNumber
saErTgNumber.description: The Transmission Group number associated with this Explicit Route.

saErOperState.name: saErOperState
saErOperState.description: The current operational state of the Explicit Route.

saVrTable.name: saVrTable
saVrTable.description: This table contains information about virtual routes between this subarea and other network subareas. Virtual routes are logical connections between subareas and are mapped to explicit routes.

saVrEntry.name: saVrEntry
saVrEntry.description: This entry contains information about a virtual route. All variables are read-only.

saVrT5nodeIndex.name: saVrT5nodeIndex
saVrT5nodeIndex.description: Index in the t5nodetable of the t5node this virtual route is associated with.

saVrErNumber.name: saVrErNumber
saVrErNumber.description: The expicit route to which this virtual route belongs.

saVrNumber.name: saVrNumber
saVrNumber.description: The number of the Virtual Route.

saVrTransmissionPriority.name: saVrTransmissionPriority
saVrTransmissionPriority.description: The transmission priority for this virtual route.

saVrWindowSize.name: saVrWindowSize
saVrWindowSize.description: The initial window size for this virtual route.

saVrMinWindowSize.name: saVrMinWindowSize
saVrMinWindowSize.description: The minimum window size for this virtual route.

saVrMaxWindowSize.name: saVrMaxWindowSize
saVrMaxWindowSize.description: The maximum window size for this virtual route.

saVrPacingCount.name: saVrPacingCount
saVrPacingCount.description: The pacing count for this virtual route.

saTgTable.name: saTgTable
saTgTable.description: This table contains information about transmission groups between this subarea and other network subareas. Entries are dynamically added to this table as they are learned from TG link activations.

saTgEntry.name: saTgEntry
saTgEntry.description: This entry contains information about a transmission group.

saTgT5nodeIndex.name: saTgT5nodeIndex
saTgT5nodeIndex.description: Index in the t5nodetable of the t5node this transmission group is associated with.

saTgNumber.name: saTgNumber
saTgNumber.description: The number of this transmission group.

saTgAdjacentSubarea.name: saTgAdjacentSubarea
saTgAdjacentSubarea.description: The adjacent subarea number with which this transmission group is associated.

saTgOperState.name: saTgOperState
saTgOperState.description: The current operational state of this transmission group.

saTgMaxSendPiuSize.name: saTgMaxSendPiuSize
saTgMaxSendPiuSize.description: The maximum Path Information Unit size in bytes that may be sent on this Tranmission Group.

saTgMaxReceivePiuSize.name: saTgMaxReceivePiuSize
saTgMaxReceivePiuSize.description: The maximum Path Information Unit size in bytes that may be received on this Tranmission Group.

saTgActiveTime.name: saTgActiveTime
saTgActiveTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when this transmission group became active.

saTgLastStateChange.name: saTgLastStateChange
saTgLastStateChange.description: The value of sysUpTime when the last state change occurred.

saTgSentBytes.name: saTgSentBytes
saTgSentBytes.description: The number of bytes sent on this transmission group.

saTgReceivedBytes.name: saTgReceivedBytes
saTgReceivedBytes.description: The number of bytes received on transmission group.

saTgSentBtus.name: saTgSentBtus
saTgSentBtus.description: The number of Basic Transmission Units sent on this transmission group.

saTgReceivedBtus.name: saTgReceivedBtus
saTgReceivedBtus.description: The number of Basic Transmission Units received on this transmission group.

saTgLinkTable.name: saTgLinkTable
saTgLinkTable.description: This table contains an entry for each link which may be used for a transmission group. The links are not associated with a transmission group until saTgLinkOperState is active (2).

saTgLinkEntry.name: saTgLinkEntry
saTgLinkEntry.description: Contains configuration and state information about TG links. Variables have read-only access. The variable saTgLinkAdminState has read-write access and is used to control a TG link.

saTgLinkT5nodeIndex.name: saTgLinkT5nodeIndex
saTgLinkT5nodeIndex.description: Identifies the Type 5 node with which this transmission group link is associated.

saTgLinkIndex.name: saTgLinkIndex
saTgLinkIndex.description: Unique index of this transmisson group link. The value is assigned by the agent and is unique among TG and PU links.

saTgLinkTgNumber.name: saTgLinkTgNumber
saTgLinkTgNumber.description: The transmission group number to which this link is associated. Contains a value of zero (0) when saTgLinkOperState is inactive(1).

saTgLinkAdjacentSubarea.name: saTgLinkAdjacentSubarea
saTgLinkAdjacentSubarea.description: The adjacent subarea number with which this transmission group is associated. Contains a value of zero when saTgLinkOperState in inactive(1).

saTgLinkName.name: saTgLinkName
saTgLinkName.description: The administratively assigned name of the transmission group link.

saTgLinkOperState.name: saTgLinkOperState
saTgLinkOperState.description: The current operational state of this transmission group link.

saTgLinkAdminState.name: saTgLinkAdminState
saTgLinkAdminState.description: Used by the Management Station to control the transmission group Link. Values up (2) and down (3) can be read or written, while value other (1) is read-only and indicates that this variable has not been set since reboot.

saTgLinkType.name: saTgLinkType
saTgLinkType.description: The type of transmission group link.

saTgLinkSpecific.name: saTgLinkSpecific
saTgLinkSpecific.description: A row in a table specific for the link. It is the object identifier representing the instance of the index variable in one of the snaLink tables from this MIB.

saTgLinkActiveTime.name: saTgLinkActiveTime
saTgLinkActiveTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when this TG link became active.

saTgLinkLastStateChange.name: saTgLinkLastStateChange
saTgLinkLastStateChange.description: The value of sysUptime when the last state change occurred.

saTgLinkSentBytes.name: saTgLinkSentBytes
saTgLinkSentBytes.description: The number of bytes sent on this TG link.

saTgLinkReceivedBytes.name: saTgLinkReceivedBytes
saTgLinkReceivedBytes.description: The number of bytes received on this TG link.

saTgLinkSentBtus.name: saTgLinkSentBtus
saTgLinkSentBtus.description: The number of Basic Transmission Units sent on this TG link.

saTgLinkReceivedBtus.name: saTgLinkReceivedBtus
saTgLinkReceivedBtus.description: The number of Basic Transmission Units received on this TG link.

t2nodeTable.name: t2nodeTable
t2nodeTable.description: This table contains all configured and dynamic parameters of type 2 nodes have read-only access. There is also one control parameter, t2nodeAdminState which has read-write access. The link specific parameters are contained in a row of a separate table referenced by the snaLinkSpecific object.

t2nodeEntry.name: t2nodeEntry
t2nodeEntry.description: Entry contains all parameters of one type 2 node. They have read-only access. The entry is created by the Agent. The variable t2nodeAdminState has read-write access and is used to start or stop the node.

t2nodeT5nodeIndex.name: t2nodeT5nodeIndex
t2nodeT5nodeIndex.description: Index in the t5nodeTable to which this t2node is associated.

t2nodeIndex.name: t2nodeIndex
t2nodeIndex.description: Used to index the instances of objects assigned by the Agent.

t2nodeName.name: t2nodeName
t2nodeName.description: The value identifies the name of the Node.

t2nodeType.name: t2nodeType
t2nodeType.description: This value identifies the type of Node.

t2nodeBlockNum.name: t2nodeBlockNum
t2nodeBlockNum.description: The value identifies the block number for this Node instance. It is the first 3 hexadecimal digits of the t2node id.

t2nodeIdNum.name: t2nodeIdNum
t2nodeIdNum.description: The value identifies the ID number for this Node instance. This is the last 5 hexadecimal digits of the t2node id.

t2nodeMaxPiu.name: t2nodeMaxPiu
t2nodeMaxPiu.description: Maximum number of octets that can be exchanged by this PU in one Pathcontrol Information Unit (PIU).

t2nodeLinkType.name: t2nodeLinkType
t2nodeLinkType.description: The type of link protocol used for this PU.

t2nodeLinkSpecific.name: t2nodeLinkSpecific
t2nodeLinkSpecific.description: The row in a table specific for the link. It is the object identifier representing the instance of the index variable in one of the snaLink tables from this MIB.

t2nodeOperState.name: t2nodeOperState
t2nodeOperState.description: The operational state of the type 2 Node.

t2nodeAdminState.name: t2nodeAdminState
t2nodeAdminState.description: The administrative state of the type 2 Node and is used by the Management Station to start or stop the Node. The values that can be read and written are: start (2) - this value has to be used to start, stop (3) - this value has to be used to stop. The values that can be read only are: other (1) - this value indicates that the variable has not been set after reboot.

t2nodeStartTime.name: t2nodeStartTime
t2nodeStartTime.description: The value of sysUpTime at type 2 Node activation.

t2nodeLastStateChange.name: t2nodeLastStateChange
t2nodeLastStateChange.description: The value of sysUpTime at the last state change of the type 2 Node.

t2nodeActFailureReason.name: t2nodeActFailureReason
t2nodeActFailureReason.description: The sense code for the activation failure. It will be sent in the trap t2NodeActFailTrap.

t2nodeStatsTable.name: t2nodeStatsTable
t2nodeStatsTable.description: This table contains the dynamic parameters which have read-only access. The entries in this table augment the entries in the t2nodeTable and cannot be created by Management Station.

t2nodeStatsEntry.name: t2nodeStatsEntry
t2nodeStatsEntry.description: The entry contains parameters which describe the statistics of one t2node. They have read-only access. The counters represent traffic for all kinds of sessions: LU-LU, SSCP-PU, and SSCP-LU. The entry is created by the Agent.

t2nodeStatsT5nodeIndex.name: t2nodeStatsT5nodeIndex
t2nodeStatsT5nodeIndex.description: Index in the t5nodeTable to which this t2node is associated.

t2nodeStatsIndex.name: t2nodeStatsIndex
t2nodeStatsIndex.description: The instance of the entry parameters. The index value is taken by the Agent from t2nodeIndex.

t2nodeStatsSentBytes.name: t2nodeStatsSentBytes
t2nodeStatsSentBytes.description: The number of bytes sent by this Node.

t2nodeStatsReceivedBytes.name: t2nodeStatsReceivedBytes
t2nodeStatsReceivedBytes.description: The number of bytes received by this Node.

t2nodeStatsSentPius.name: t2nodeStatsSentPius
t2nodeStatsSentPius.description: The number of PIUs sent by this Node.

t2nodeStatsReceivedPius.name: t2nodeStatsReceivedPius
t2nodeStatsReceivedPius.description: The number of PIUs received by this Node.

t2nodeStatsSentNegativeResps.name: t2nodeStatsSentNegativeResps
t2nodeStatsSentNegativeResps.description: The number of negative responses sent by this Node.

t2nodeStatsReceivedNegativeResps.name: t2nodeStatsReceivedNegativeResps
t2nodeStatsReceivedNegativeResps.description: The number of negative responses received by this Node.

t2nodeStatsActiveLus.name: t2nodeStatsActiveLus
t2nodeStatsActiveLus.description: The number of LUs currently active on this PU.

t2nodeStatsActLus.name: t2nodeStatsActLus
t2nodeStatsActLus.description: The number of LUs on this type 2 Node which have active SSCP-LU sessions.

t2nodeStatsInActLus.name: t2nodeStatsInActLus
t2nodeStatsInActLus.description: The number of LUs on this type 2 Node which do not have active SSCP-LU sessions.

t2nodeStatsBindLus.name: t2nodeStatsBindLus
t2nodeStatsBindLus.description: The number of LUs on this type 2 Node which have received and acknowledged a BIND request.

snaLuTable.name: snaLuTable
snaLuTable.description: This table contains configuration and state information relating to LUs.

snaLuEntry.name: snaLuEntry
snaLuEntry.description: Contains configuration and state objects relating to an LU. All have read-only access with the exeption of snaLuAdminState which has read-write access and is used by the Management station to control the state of the LU.

snaLuT5nodeIndex.name: snaLuT5nodeIndex
snaLuT5nodeIndex.description: Index in the t5nodeTable to which this LU is associated.

snaLuT2nodeIndex.name: snaLuT2nodeIndex
snaLuT2nodeIndex.description: Index in the t2nodeTable of the type 2 Node with which this LU is associated.

snaLuIndex.name: snaLuIndex
snaLuIndex.description: This value identifies a unique index for an LU instance within a type 2 Node.

snaLuName.name: snaLuName
snaLuName.description: The SNA name for this LU.

snaLuType.name: snaLuType
snaLuType.description: Identifies whether the LU is Type 0, 1, 2, 3 or 6.2

snaLuLocalAddress.name: snaLuLocalAddress
snaLuLocalAddress.description: The local address for this LU. It is a byte with a value ranging in size from 0 to 255. For dependent LUs this value ranges from 1 to 255. For independent Lus this value is always 0.

snaLuUserName.name: snaLuUserName
snaLuUserName.description: The name of the non-sna terminal or SNA LU that is using this LU. This value does not apply to all LUs and contains a zero length string if not known or does not apply.

snaLuPoolName.name: snaLuPoolName
snaLuPoolName.description: The name of the LU pool to which this LU belongs. An LU Pool is configured by the user. It contains a group of LUs any of which can be assigned to a user requesting an LU by the Pool name. May be a zero length string if this LU does not belong to a pool.

snaLuOperState.name: snaLuOperState
snaLuOperState.description: The current operational state of this LU: For dependent LUs active(2) indicates the SSCP-LU session is active. For Independent LUs active(2) indicates that the LU is able to send or receive BINDs.

snaLuAdminState.name: snaLuAdminState
snaLuAdminState.description: This object is used by a management station to control the LU. Values up(2) and down(3) can be read or written, while a value other(1) is read-only and indicates that this variable has not been set since reboot.

snaLuLastStateChange.name: snaLuLastStateChange
snaLuLastStateChange.description: The value of sysUpTime when the last state change occurred.

snaLuActiveTime.name: snaLuActiveTime
snaLuActiveTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when this LU becomes active.

snaLuBindFailureReason.name: snaLuBindFailureReason
snaLuBindFailureReason.description: The sense code when there is a bind failure.

applicationLuTable.name: applicationLuTable
applicationLuTable.description: Table of application LUs configuration and operational information.

appLuEntry.name: appLuEntry
appLuEntry.description: Contains configuration and operational variables of an application LU. Variables are read-only with the exception of appLuAdminState which has read-write access and is used by the Management station to control the state of the Application LU.

appLuT5nodeIndex.name: appLuT5nodeIndex
appLuT5nodeIndex.description: Index in the t5nodeTable to which this application LU is associated.

appLuIndex.name: appLuIndex
appLuIndex.description: Unique index of an application LU.

appLuName.name: appLuName
appLuName.description: Configured name for this application LU.

appLuConversionType.name: appLuConversionType
appLuConversionType.description: Indicates the type of protocol conversion being performed on behalf of the application LU.

appLuHostInterfaceType.name: appLuHostInterfaceType
appLuHostInterfaceType.description: Identifies the type of application interface used by this application LU.

appLuApplicationName.name: appLuApplicationName
appLuApplicationName.description: The name of the host application which uses this application LU.

appLuGatewayName.name: appLuGatewayName
appLuGatewayName.description: The name of the application gateway. The gateway is used to group application LUs together for management purposes.

appLuAdminState.name: appLuAdminState
appLuAdminState.description: Used by the Management Station to control the Application LU. Values up (2) and down (3) can be read or written, while value other (1) is read-only and indicates that this variable has not been set since reboot.

appLuOperState.name: appLuOperState
appLuOperState.description: The current operational state of this application LU: whether it is inactive, active, or has one of more active sessions.

appLuActiveTime.name: appLuActiveTime
appLuActiveTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when this application LU becomes active.

appLuLastStateChange.name: appLuLastStateChange
appLuLastStateChange.description: The value of sysUpTime when the last state change occurred.

appLuBindFailureReason.name: appLuBindFailureReason
